  "text": "The down-conversion is performed by a current commutating passive mixer, which has the superior advantages of low flicker noise and high linearity with low supply voltage [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . As shown in Fig. 3 , the mixer consists of a current transconductor converting the input signal voltage to current, a double-balanced switching quad, and a bandwidth programmable TIA utilized to attenuate the out-of-band interferences and drive the following stage such as low-pass filter or delta-sigma analog-todigital converter.",
